EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to state financial administration; revising
provisions governing deposits of public money under
certain circumstances; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, with certain exceptions, all public money received by every
2 state officer, department or commission must be: (1) deposited on or before
3 Thursday of each week; and (2) if, on any day the money accumulated for deposit
4 is $10,000 or more, deposited not later than the next working day. However, if the
5 Department of Wildlife accumulates $10,000 or more, the money must be deposited
6 within 10 working days. (NRS 353.250) This bill also exempts the Division of State
7 Parks of the State Department of Conservation and Natural Resources from the
8 requirement to deposit $10,000 or more accumulated during any day by the next
9 working day and requires the Division to instead deposit the money within 10
10 working days.
