THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 353.250 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 353.250 1. The State Treasurer shall designate the financial
3 institutions into which money received by a state officer, department
4 or commission must be deposited.
5 2. Except as otherwise provided in subsections 3, 4 and 5,
6 every state officer, department or commission which receives or
7 which may receive any money of the State of Nevada or for its use
8 and benefit shall deposit on or before Thursday of each week, in a
9 financial institution designated by the State Treasurer to the credit of
10 the State Treasurer’s Account, all money received by that officer,
11 department or commission during the previous week.
12 3. Except as otherwise provided in subsections 4 and 5, if on
13 any day the money accumulated for deposit is $10,000 or more, a
14 deposit must be made not later than the next working day.
15 4. If the Department of Wildlife or the Division of State Parks
16 of the State Department of Conservation and Natural Resources
17 accumulates for deposit $10,000 or more on any day, the money
18 must be deposited within 10 working days.
19 5. Except as otherwise provided in this subsection, if the
20 Division of Welfare and Supportive Services of the Department of
21 Health and Human Services accumulates for deposit $10,000 or
22 more in child support payments on any day, the money must be
23 deposited within 2 working days after its accumulation. Any such
24 money for which the Division is unable to identify the obligee
25 within 2 working days after its accumulation must, within 5 working
26 days after its accumulation, be:
27 (a) Deposited, if the Division is able to identify the obligee.
28 (b) Returned to the payor, if the Division is unable to identify
29 the obligee.
30 6. Every officer, department or commission which is required
31 to deposit money with the State Treasurer shall comply with that
32 requirement by depositing the money in a financial institution
33 designated by the State Treasurer to the credit of the State
34 Treasurer’s Account.
35 7. Every officer, head of any department or commissioner who
36 fails to comply with the provisions of this section is guilty of a
37 misdemeanor in office.
38 8. As used in this section, “financial institution” means a bank,
39 savings and loan association, savings bank, thrift company or credit
40 union regulated pursuant to title 55 of NRS.
